---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  {/* Profile */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify leading-relaxed max-w-4xl">
    <p class="mb-3">
      Cloud &amp; DevOps Engineer with around <strong>2 years</strong> of experience
      building secure, automated, and scalable cloud infrastructures using{" "}
      <strong>AWS</strong>, <strong>Kubernetes</strong>, and <strong>Terraform</strong>.
      I focus on DevSecOps practices, observability, and cost-efficiency to keep
      systems reliable and easy to operate.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-3">
      With roughly <strong>3 years</strong> in full-stack development, I bridge
      application concerns with cloud architecture—prioritizing clean design,
      automation, and CI/CD so teams can ship faster with confidence. As a
      Technical Lead at <strong>Day Truck</strong>, I drive cloud, DevOps, and
      observability initiatives across on-prem and cloud environments.
    </p>
    <p>
      Languages: Arabic (native), French (C1), English (C1), German (B1). Location:
      Tunisia.
    </p>
  </div>

  {/* Education */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Engineering Degree – National Engineering School of Gabes (ENIG)"
      subtitle="2023 · Process Engineering · Gabès, Tunisia"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Preparatory Classes – Higher Institute of Applied Sciences and Technology of Gabes (ISSAT)"
      subtitle="2020 · PC Preparatory Cycle · Gabès, Tunisia"
    />
  </div>

  {/* Experience */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10 grid gap-4">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Cloud & DevOps Engineer – Technical Lead · Day Truck"
      subtitle="May 2024 – Present · Tunisia (On-site)"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
        <li>
          Designed and deployed a hybrid infrastructure combining{" "}
          <strong>AWS Cloud</strong> and an on-premise dedicated server for increased
          flexibility and control.
        </li>
        <li>
          Automated infrastructure provisioning using <strong>Terraform</strong>, enabling
          consistent, repeatable, and auditable changes.
        </li>
        <li>
          Built multi-stage <strong>CI/CD pipelines</strong> with Jenkins (build, test,
          staging, production) to streamline delivery workflows.
        </li>
        <li>
          Integrated <strong>Trivy</strong> (container scanning) and{" "}
          <strong>SonarQube</strong> (code quality) into CI/CD pipelines to enforce
          security and quality gates.
        </li>
        <li>
          Implemented monitoring and observability using{" "}
          <strong>AWS CloudWatch</strong> and Container Insights (metrics, logs,
          alerts) to improve reliability.
        </li>
        <li>
          Operated <strong>Kubernetes in production</strong>: on-premise cluster on
          dedicated server + <strong>AWS EKS</strong> for production workloads.
        </li>
        <li>
          Reduced AWS costs by approximately <strong>15%</strong> through resource
          right-sizing and infrastructure tuning.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Full Stack Developer · Vintonet"
      subtitle="Jan 2024 – Apr 2024 · Tunisia (On-site)"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
        <li>
          Developed <strong>Mecafix</strong>, an OCR-based platform with geolocation and
          chat, using <strong>Next.js</strong> and <strong>Laravel</strong>.
        </li>
        <li>
          Deployed the platform on <strong>Clever Cloud</strong> with automated builds and
          environment configuration.
        </li>
        <li>
          Designed modular and secure APIs, optimized data access patterns, and
          improved backend performance and security.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Full Stack Developer (Freelance)"
      subtitle="Jul 2021 – Apr 2024 · Remote"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
        <li>
          Delivered <strong>10+ end-to-end applications</strong> for clients using React,
          Laravel, WordPress, and custom stacks.
        </li>
        <li>
          Implemented CI/CD workflows and automated deployments on VPS/Cloud
          hosts with a focus on security and maintainability.
        </li>
        <li>
          Improved availability and delivery speed through automation and
          monitoring across hosting environments.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Web Developer · Iris Hotel & Thalasso"
      subtitle="Jul 2021 – Jul 2023 · Tunisia (Remote)"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
        <li>
          Built and optimized websites using <strong>PHP</strong> and{" "}
          <strong>WordPress</strong>, with a focus on performance, SEO, and content
          management.
        </li>
        <li>Improved user experience, loading times, and search visibility.</li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="End-of-Study Intern · Groupe Chimique Tunisien"
      subtitle="Feb 2023 – Jun 2023 · Gabès, Tunisia"
    >
      <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
        <li>
          Completed an end-of-study industrial engineering project, combining
          technical analysis and process optimization.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  {/* Certifications */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate · Amazon Web Services</li>
    <li>Oracle Cloud Infrastructure 2025 Certified DevOps Professional · Oracle</li>
    <li>ISO/IEC 27001:2022 Lead Auditor</li>
    <li>Meta Full-Stack Engineer Certificate · Meta</li>
    <li>Meta Front-End Developer &amp; Meta Back-End Developer · Meta</li>
    <li>
      Google Cybersecurity Specialization &amp; Google IT Support Professional
      Certificate
    </li>
    <li>Microsoft Certified: Azure Fundamentals · AZ-900</li>
    <li>
      Microsoft Certified: Security, Compliance, and Identity Fundamentals
    </li>
    <li>GitHub Foundations · GitHub</li>
    <li>Scrum Foundation Professional Certification (SFPC) · CertiProf</li>
    <li>Six Sigma Yellow Belt · 6sigmastudy</li>
    <li>EF SET English Certificate · C1 Level</li>
    <li>ECL German B1 Certificate</li>
  </ul>

  {/* GitHub & Personal Projects */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">GitHub &amp; Personal Projects</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/jaafar-harabi/aws-terraform-infra-blueprint"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline underline-offset-4"
      >
        aws-terraform-infra-blueprint
      </a>{" "}
      – AWS IaC blueprint (VPC, EKS, RDS, S3, IAM) with GitHub Actions CI.
    </li>
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/jaafar-harabi/secure-task-api-devsecops"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline underline-offset-4"
      >
        Secure Task API
      </a>{" "}
      – Node.js/TypeScript API with PostgreSQL, Docker, and a DevSecOps-focused
      pipeline.
    </li>
    <li>
      Ranked among the most active GitHub contributors in Tunisia on{" "}
      <a
        href="https://committers.top/tunisia_private"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
        class="underline underline-offset-4"
      >
        committers.top
      </a>
      .
    </li>
  </ul>

  {/* Skills */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6 mb-8 gap-2">
    <li>
      <strong>Cloud:</strong> AWS, Azure, GCP, OVHcloud
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Containers:</strong> Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, ArgoCD
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>IaC &amp; CI/CD:</strong> Terraform, Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, GitHub
      Actions, Ansible
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>DevSecOps &amp; Security:</strong> Vault, Trivy, SonarQube,
      SAST/SCA, secret scanning, IAM, least-privilege
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Monitoring &amp; Observability:</strong> CloudWatch, Prometheus,
      Grafana, ELK
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Languages &amp; Scripting:</strong> Python, Bash, PowerShell,
      JavaScript/TypeScript, PHP, Java, Go
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Frameworks:</strong> React, Next.js, Laravel, NestJS, Spring Boot
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Databases:</strong> MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Tools:</strong> Linux (Ubuntu, Debian), Git, Jira, Slack
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Practices:</strong> CI/CD, GitOps, Infrastructure as Code,
      Cloud-Native Architecture
    </li>
  </ul>

  {/* Languages */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Languages</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-8 grid gap-1">
    <li>Arabic – Native or bilingual proficiency</li>
    <li>French – Full professional proficiency (C1)</li>
    <li>English – Full professional proficiency (C1)</li>
    <li>German – Intermediate / B1</li>
  </ul>

  {/* Interests */}
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Interests</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-1">
    <li>Chess</li>
    <li>Reading &amp; technology research</li>
    <li>Cloud-native architectures &amp; DevOps tooling</li>
    <li>Security, automation, and observability</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
